goal: What are the differences between plant-based and animal-based protein sources?
answer:
[🔒CLASSIC] The main difference between plant-based and animal-based protein sources is where they come from. Plant-based proteins come from plants, such as legumes, nuts, seeds, and soy, while animal-based proteins come from animals, such as meat, dairy, and eggs. Plant-based proteins generally contain less saturated fat and fewer calories than animal-based proteins, and they are typically richer in fiber, vitamins, and minerals. Animal-based proteins, on the other hand, are complete proteins, meaning they provide all the essential amino acids that the body needs to function properly. Some plant-based proteins, such as soy, quinoa, and buckwheat, are also complete proteins.
